# Long-Running Operations Notification

When an agent operation takes more than **5 minutes**, automatically send SMS to the current user after it completes (success or failure).

## User / SMS lookup

Use `$env:USERNAME` to get the SMS number. Same lookup as DedgePsh (single source of truth):

```powershell
$smsNumber = switch ($env:USERNAME) {
    "FKGEISTA" { "+4797188358" }
    "FKSVEERI" { "+4795762742" }
    "FKMISTA"  { "+4799348397" }
    "FKCELERI" { "+4745269945" }
    default    { "+4797188358" }
}
```

## Sending SMS

Assume **GlobalFunctions** is on PsModulePath (same as DedgePsh). Before sending:

```powershell
Import-Module GlobalFunctions -Force
Send-Sms -Receiver $smsNumber -Message "<summary>"
```

Alternatively, call the DedgePsh script if available: `C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\UtilityTools\Send-Sms\Send-Sms.ps1` with arguments `$smsNumber` and the message string.

## SMS message format

- Keep under **1024 characters** (service supports longer SMS)
- Include: **operation type**, **files/scope affected**, and **status** (success/failure)

Example: `DedgeAuth: PostgreSQL migration + per-app roles. 8 files. Success.`

## When to send

- **Send:** After the long-running operation completes (success or failure)
- **Do NOT send:** Operations under 5 minutes; purely interactive or question-only turns
